Section : 1


Syntax : ls [OPTION]... [FILE]...


DESCRIPTION : used to list files and directory existing in the path it is in
and you can list files in a particular directory via writting ls /name_directory
and you can used it to list inforomation about file or directory such as permession or size or ownership ... via adding option to the command 


Example 1 :  ls -i file1
to list file1 with inode number 


Example 2 : ls -ali 
to list all files even hiddin files and all directory and links 
list all of them with inode number and ,use a long listing format
 such as list ownership , group , size , modifaction data 
